OL,3,CCouncil to debate 'transparency' in
OL,4,Casylum seeker accommodation
OL,6,FIt will call on the UK Government to
OL,7,Fend the use of private sector agents
OL,8,Fand to scrap profit-making
OL,9,Farrangements, that Wrexham Council
OL,10,Fsays "allow millions of pounds of
OL,11,Ftaxpayers' money to be extracted from
OL,12,Fthe situation".
OL,14,FA private company called Clearsprings,
OL,15,Fwho have a contract from the UK
OL,16,FGovernment to find places to house
OL,17,Fasylum seekers, have proposed Plas yn
OL,18,FRhos in Rhosllanercrugog as a
OL,19,Fpotential option. They have suggested
OL,20,Fthis could be used to accommodate 70
OL,21,Fpeople.
