OL,3,CCouncil to debate 'transparency' in
OL,4,Casylum seeker accommodation
OL,6,F"The Home Office is not being open or
OL,7,Ftransparent in the way it deals with
OL,8,Fasylum dispersal ` there is a complete
OL,9,Flack of adequate consultation with
OL,10,Flocal councils.
OL,12,F"Using private sector agents to
OL,13,Fidentify asylum accommodation is
OL,14,Fcompletely unfair on taxpayers, and
OL,15,Fthe consultation time-frames are
OL,16,Fcompletely unrealistic, and the system
OL,17,Fhas to change.
